# Python build artifacts
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# AI-session handoff folder.  Holds notes the user wants kept on
# the local working copy across Claude sessions but NOT pushed to
# the public repo.  Self-managed by the AI at end-of-session.
# Anything under hand_off/ is local-only; safe to wipe.
hand_off/

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~

# Claude Code local state -- per-user settings + permissions cache
# generated by the Claude Code CLI as it runs.  Machine-specific,
# never wanted in the shared repo.  CLAUDE.md (the orientation file
# at repo root) IS tracked; this rule only excludes the dotfile dir.
.claude/

# Smoke-test / scratch files left by the rebuild_itemlist tool when
# we want to compare an experimental rebuild against the live file
# without overwriting it.
TheItemList.NEW.xml

# Generated cache, machine-specific (depends on which WoT version /
# platform pkgs the user has installed) and 70+ MB.  TEPY auto-builds
# this on first launch when it's missing -- see viewer.py's
# `_ensure_itemlist` post-UI hook.  Never commit.
TheItemList.xml

# Wargaming particle artwork.  Every PNG under resources/fire/ and
# resources/smoke/ is a slice of WoT's eff_tex.dds atlas, which we
# can't redistribute.  Viewer.__init__ calls
# `ensure_runtime_flipbooks()` (in cust_tools/extract_wot_fire_atlas.py)
# at startup, which re-extracts the atlas from the user's local
# particles.pkg and slices the two runtime grids
# (fire_BIG -> resources/fire/, smoke_white -> resources/smoke/) on
# first launch.  resources/fire_sets/ is the authoring-mode dump
# (every catalogued grid, ~10 subfolders); the runtime path only
# touches the two folders the viewer reads.  Cached atlas DDS lives
# at resources/_wot_eff_tex.dds.  None of this ships in the repo.
resources/_wot_eff_tex.dds
resources/fire_sets/
resources/fire/
resources/smoke/

# Legacy explosion flipbook from an earlier flipbook source -- also
# WoT-derived, no longer used by the viewer.  Listed defensively in
# case anyone still has stale copies on disk.
resources/fire_legacy_explosion/

# Default config SHIPS with the repo so new clones boot with sane
# smoke / fire tunings + an obvious place to set their WoT paths.
# The launcher's Set Paths dialog overwrites pkg_dir / res_mods /
# lookup_xml on first run -- subsequent commits would push those
# back upstream though, so don't `git add` your local copy unless
# you intend to update the shipped defaults.
#
# `tankExporterPy.json` is TRACKED (no rule below).
# `tankviewer.json` is the pre-v1.48.2 filename; gitignored so a
# stale local copy from an older session never sneaks back in.
tankviewer.json

# requirements/ folder is consumed by go.bat on first install and
# then deleted; the permanent backup at resources/requirements_backup/
# is what survives.  Both should ship in the repo though, so neither
# is ignored here -- this comment is just to remind future readers.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Debug output written by the gun-recoil / tracer-trail tooling in
# viewer.py (DEBUG_FILE_DUMPS flag).  Holds per-impact screenshots,
# particle-age dumps, emit-pos dumps, fire_log.txt.  Folder is wiped
# at every startup; never useful to share.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
debug_screens/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local debug dumps written by ad-hoc Python scratch tools while
# investigating shader crashes / eff_tex layouts / etc.  Local-only.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
_dump_eff_tex_inspect/
_dump_shader_crash/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Scratch plot / analysis scripts pinned to specific tanks
# (T-30, M3 Stuart, Tiger, T110E4 etc.).  Generated to investigate
# the track-physics rewrite; the production diagnostic is
# `cust_tools/analyze_track_spline.py`.  These per-tank one-offs are
# left on the working tree but not pushed.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
_plot_t30_*.py
cust_tools/plot_chain_runtime.py
cust_tools/plot_for_claude.py
cust_tools/plot_gravity_affect.py
cust_tools/plot_homie_T110E4.py
cust_tools/plot_homie_Tiger.py
cust_tools/plot_homie_compare.py
cust_tools/plot_m3_stuart_spline.py
cust_tools/plot_t30_dense_hub_anchors.py
cust_tools/plot_t30_partial_support.py
cust_tools/plot_t30_spline_fit.py
cust_tools/plot_t30_spline_math.py
cust_tools/plot_t30_wheel_wrap_compare.py
cust_tools/test_force_balance.py
cust_tools/test_wheel_extract.py

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Other local-only debug artefacts.
#   `gun_recoil_dump.txt` -- one-off dump from the recoil byte-ID hunt.
#   `math_images/`         -- runtime plot output dir (cust_tools writes
#                              here via `analyze_track_spline.py` etc.).
#   `test_runs/`           -- F3-recorder output captures (per-frame
#                              field-schema CSV / JSON).
#   `tanks_index.txt`      -- local pkg / vehicle catalog cache.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
gun_recoil_dump.txt
math_images/
test_runs/
tanks_index.txt

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Worktree directories created by `git worktree add` for parallel
# Claude / branch experiments.  Each subfolder is its own branch
# checkout; never push them up through master.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
experiment/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sibling project; lives next to tankExporterPy but doesn't belong
# in this repo.  Tracked separately.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
nuTerraPy/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vehicle effects binary cache extracted from WoT pkgs.  Same
# redistribution rules as the eff_tex atlas -- can't ship Wargaming
# bytes.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
vfxbin/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gun-trail flipbook frames extracted from WoT's eff_tex.dds atlas
# (same rule as resources/fire/ + resources/smoke/ above).
# `Viewer.__init__ -> ensure_runtime_flipbooks()` re-extracts on
# first launch.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
resources/gun_trail/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Heightmaps / reference images of unknown / WoT provenance.
# Conservatively excluded -- we never want to ship Wargaming
# pixels we didn't authorise to redistribute.  The authored
# sand textures (resources/sand_painted*) DO ship.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
resources/heightmap.png
reference/heightmap.png
reference/T-30 rewf pic.png
resources/d1yeqz9-*.jpg

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Procedural sand textures generated by
# `cust_tools/paint_sand_desert.py`.  Big (60-85 MB PNGs) and
# trivially reproducible -- the painter script ships, so anyone
# can regenerate.  Don't push the binaries themselves.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
resources/sand.png
resources/sand_painted.png
resources/sand_painted_height.png
